INSTALLATION (REQUIRED DEPENDECIES):

CORE PACKAGES:
	gcc
	make
	python
	
Numpy:
	sudo apt-get install python-numpy

YASM:
	sudo apt-get install yasm

FFMPEG:
	tar xvfj ffmpeg-2.4.2.tar.bz2
	cd ffmpeg-2.4.2
	./configure
	sudo make install
	
PYDUB:
	tar xvfz pydub-0.9.3.tar.gz
	cd pydub-0.9.3
	sudo python setup.py install

PYSYNTH:
	tar xvfz PySynth-1.0.1.tar.gz
	cd PySynth-1.0.1
	sudo python setup.py install

NARRATIVES 2.0:
	How to run .wav visualization code:
	1. Download and install processing: https://processing.org/download/
	2. Open the processing IDE
	3. In the processing IDE, open the file ~/cpsc410/Narratives2_ESS2/Narratives2_ESS2/Narratives2_ESS2.pde
	4. In the processing IDE, from options on top bar select Sketch->Add File
        a) Select the file: ~/cpsc410/Narratives2_ESS2/Narratives2_ESS2/lib/Ess/library/Ess.jar and click Open
	5. You should now be able to click on the Run button (play icon) in the IDE and run the out.wav file
	6. To export the app as an executable script, click on the Export Application button in the IDE
	   This creates an executable that you can click on and run: Narratives2_ESS2/Narratives2_ESS2/application.linux64/Narratives2_ESS2

	This was done on 64 bit Linux